title: How Chase Oliver’s Senate Run Helped Lead to a Runoff in Georgia
description: Chase Oliver won a little more than 2 percent of the vote. His politics are unusual: He describes himself as “armed and gay.”
dc:creator: Richard Fausset

media:content.media:description: In recent years, a couple of Libertarian Party candidates have had an outsized influence, particularly in elections that have turned on a few percentage points.
